Parallelizing Counting Sort using threads in Java requires dividing the array into equal segments and then processing each segment in a separate thread. After local counting is done, we then merge the results synchronously.

Here's a basic example of a parallelized Counting Sort in Java:

```java
import java.util.Arrays;
import java.util.concurrent.atomic.AtomicIntegerArray;

public class ParallelCountingSort {
    private static final int MAX_VALUE = 100; // Assuming that the input array values will be from 0 to MAX_VALUE

    public static void parallelCountingSort(int[] arr, int numThreads) throws InterruptedException {
        AtomicIntegerArray countArray = new AtomicIntegerArray(MAX_VALUE + 1);
        Thread[] threads = new Thread[numThreads];

        // Create and start threads
        for (int t = 0; t < numThreads; t++) {
            final int start = (int) ((long) t * arr.length / numThreads);
            final int end = (int) ((long) (t + 1) * arr.length / numThreads);
            threads[t] = new Thread(() -> {
                for (int i = start; i < end; i++) {
                    countArray.getAndIncrement(arr[i]);
                }
            });
            threads[t].start();
        }

        // Wait for all threads to finish
        for (Thread thread : threads) {
            thread.join();
        }

        // Combine the counted values back into the original array
        int index = 0;
        for (int i = 0; i <= MAX_VALUE; i++) {
            while (countArray.get(i) > 0) {
                arr[index++] = i;
                countArray.decrementAndGet(i);
            }
        }
    }

    public static void main(String[] args) throws InterruptedException {
        int[] array = {15, 22, 8, 13, 27, 12, 5, 18, 29, 25, 11, 3, 1, 50};
        int numThreads = Runtime.getRuntime().availableProcessors();

        System.out.println("Original array: " + Arrays.toString(array));

        parallelCountingSort(array, numThreads);

        System.out.println("Sorted array: " + Arrays.toString(array));
    }
}
```

